<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1650] HBASE-1551 broke the ability to manage non-regionserver start-up/shut down. ie: you cant start/stop thrift on a cluster anymore</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1650</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I used to be able to do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bin/hbase-daemons.sh stop thrift&lt;br/&gt;
bin/hbase-daemons.sh start thrift&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t anymore. We can&apos;t manage anything but regionservers and zookeeper with this script now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
